Ethiopian officials, including this man, Ambassador Shamebo Fitamo, the @mfaethiopia's Director General for Middle East Affairs, had opposed repatriations, with Ambassador Shamebo saying quite bluntly here that returnees would endanger 110 million people. 
https://t.co/rljwqvoZbS

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: The first @flyethiopian  non evacuation flight that lifted off from Beirut to Addis Ababa sold tickets at 680 plus quarantine fees. A total of 13 passengers were aboard that flight as migrants decried the airliner's price gouging. https://t.co/revLTn5npl

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: It must be clarified that Ethiopia's National Carrier is owed no praise whatsoever. Domestic workers are completely dependent on evacuation flights because the airline has hiked the prices of one way Beirut to Addis flights considerably. No this doesn't include quarantine fees. https://t.co/fF2QYgBn6o

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: It's great that negotiations ended with the waving of fees. If you want clarity into how that happened, you'd have to ask Ethiopian activists who attended in lieu of Ethiopia's absent diplomats. Among those who negotiated on behalf of Ethiopian migrants, is @tsigereda_B.

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: Here's the thing: there are 1163 Ethiopian women who have returned from Beirut since January after having paid 550$. No word on whether they will be reimbursed. Also, there is no word on whether anything will be done to repatriate the thousands more who didn't have 550$ to spare. https://t.co/h3fYgy4Fh4

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: The embassies of Ghana, Nigeria, Philippines and Bangladesh. Representing Ethiopia? No diplomats...but activists from @EgnaLegnaDWU and Mesewat. Lebanese feminist organization KAFA organized the discussions with the Lebanese gov...which lasted from November to March. https://t.co/8D31mOwryV

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: The real people who ought to be thanked for this are the diplomats and activists who negotiated with the Lebanese government. Lebanon recently waived all immigration fees for undocumented migrants who want to return home. Among them....

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: The order to reimburse is simply righting a wrong and not something to congratulate anyone over. The women should never have been charged in the first place. In March, immigration fees plus tickets costed about ~260$, women were being forced to fork over 550$ by the consulate.

author: Zecharias Zelalem
tweet/fb text: CONFIRMED: The first returnees from Beirut yesterday landed in Addis & were reimbursed the 550$ registration fee after ample media backlash. State broadcaster @fanatelevision turned their arrival into a photo-op for about a dozen government officials from various ministries. https://t.co/lLVMbRwF8D

author: Tsedale Lemma
tweet/fb text:
This requires the availability of a  peace roadmap including Integrated Disarmament, Demobilization, & Reintegration Standards (IDDRS) along with formidable interventions by well-established negotiators & peace & security institutions that broker such conflicts. 6/6

#EndTheWar!

author: Tsedale Lemma
tweet/fb text:
..& treat the OLA rebel groups not just as "mentally deranged" few individuals, but an armed group with whom an honest & genuine peace negotiations needed to be had with.

It's also time the OLA group articulated its demands unambiguously & prepare to lay down arms...5/6

author: Tsedale Lemma
tweet/fb text:
But it is not & should not be taken as the end of the story. This can't be allowed to be the new normal. 

It's time that Ethiopia takes a page or two from other countries' experiences on peace negotiations with rebel movts. 

It's time we end party politicking & mudslinging..4/6

author: Tsedale Lemma
tweet/fb text:
...these attempts for negotiated settlement thus far. 

The result is what we kept witnessing: mothers of civilians & security forces agonizing; families losing their loved ones; the social fabric of a community being ripped apart by two warring brothers. 

It's painful!
... 3/6

author: Tsedale Lemma
tweet/fb text: Trust, the foundation of a negotiated settlement, is one of the major casualties in the two year's attempts so far for peace between the fed. & #Oromia govs on one side & the rebel groups, OLA,on the other b/se party politicking, deception & lack of sincerity have overruled.. 2/6

author: Tsedale Lemma
tweet/fb text: The possibility of a lasting peace in Western & Southern #Oromia & the political atmosphere for a negotiated settlement appear to be exhausted, sadly. The people of #Wollega & #Guji & their environs are bleeding from a double-edged frontier of a war that has no winner so far..1/6
